Central City Cross Country Invite - September 17th, 2020. We can use some help next Thursday for our cross country invite. This marks the 48th year (since 1971) we have had our meet. Awesome!

We need help handing out medals at the finish line and a few more people on parking duties. Most schools this year are choosing to hand out medals as they finish instead of a presentation at the end of the meet.

3:30pm - Parking duties start
4:30pm - Races start
HS Girls
HS Boys
MS Girls
MS Boys

Please help us continue to make this a great event!

Thanks

Please specify to her who is placing the order, a contact number, and what personalization you would like added to the blanket.

shared_text:
Central City Youth Football
July 2 at 2:17 PM ·

We just learned that there will be Columbus Area Youth Football this year! Central City's youth football program has been a part of the Columbus Area Youth Football for quite a few years. All games will more than likely be played in Columbus this year but practices will be held here in Central City. We will have more information next week and once that is received we will set sign up dates. In order to make this happen we will first need parents to commit to helping coach. If sign ups go like they have in the past we will need 2 head coaches for 3rd/4th and 1 to 2 head coaches for 5th/6th grade. Please let me know if you have interest in helping coach and stay tuned for more information on sign ups next week!
Amy
308-940-1414

post_text:
Corona 5 at 5!!! Wednesday Nights...

There was an OVERWHELMING positive public response to our first attempt at the Corona 5 at 5 two weeks ago and the Class of 2020 tribute on Friday night. So, the Corona 5 at 5 will officially be a weekly event! On Wednesday nights (at least for the rest of the school year) we be playing 5 upbeat songs at 5:00 on the Bison Stadium speakers.

We hope this event can continue to help lift the community spirits during this time. Feel free to sing and dance in your front yards with your family and friends, but keep your social distancing.

CentralCity Nebraska
Central City Police Department

Central City Public Schools
March 10 at 12:27 PM ·

Construction is progressing very well! Starting Monday, March 16th, the Middle School Entrance will no longer be accessible to enter or exit as construction will begin in that area. The Middle School Entrance will temporarily move to the Performing Arts Center Entrance (PAC) and the Middle School can be accessed from that entrance. The PAC Entrance will be used until the completion of the new entrance at the Middle School.

post_text: A big congratulations to Spencer and Ella. Because of their exceptionally high scores on their Microsoft Office Specialist exams in PowerPoint 2016 (Spencer) and Excel 2016 (Ella), they were named Nebraska's Champions. They have the opportunity to compete in Certiport’s 2020 Microsoft Office Specialist U.S. National Championship at the Gaylord Texan Resort and Convention Center in Dallas, TX, June 15-17, 2020. In addition to being named the MOS Excel 2016 champion, Ella also received 3rd place in the MOS PowerPoint 2016 competition.
text: A big congratulations to Spencer and Ella. Because of their exceptionally high scores on their Microsoft Office Specialist exams in PowerPoint 2016 (Spencer) and Excel 2016 (Ella), they were named Nebraska's Champions. They have the opportunity to compete in Certiport’s 2020 Microsoft Office Specialist U.S. National Championship at the Gaylord Texan Resort and Convention Center in Dallas, TX, June 15-17, 2020. In addition to being named the MOS Excel 2016 champion, Ella also received 3rd place in the MOS PowerPoint 2016 competition.

post_text: Congratulations to Tanner, Christian, Ella, and Spencer for earning specialist level certification in Microsoft Word, Excel, PowerPoint, and Access. Rylie, Vincent, and Kenzie earned certification in Microsoft Word, ,Excel, and PowerPoint. Tanner, Crystal, Ellie, Jasmine, Dylan, and Derek are certified in Microsoft Word. Becoming certified verifies that these students have the Information Technology skills that they will need for college and careers in today’s technology-focused job markets. Skill based learning is in high demand and these students took advantage of a great opportunity to validate their technology skills, learn new things, and persevere through rigorous challenges. Way to go!

post_text: Bison softball is two wins away from state! Central City escapes with a close win over Polk County to open districts. The girls found themselves down 5-4 heading into the last inning (7th) against Fillmore Central in the second game before exploding for 16 runs on nine hits for a 20-6 victory. Central City will play top seed Hastings Saint Cecilia tomorrow at 10:00am. Weather could change games till Friday or Saturday......TBD. Well done players and coaches.
